Changed so that returned ML gap is a float. Also improved accuracy by

Added GapEst estimation to Normal model.

Factored out a function "get_likelihood_value" that can be called from different
places.
1 It is called by infer_mean_fast which performa a binary search.
2 It is called by "get_likelihood_function" that wants all the values on the
curve (up to some precision).

This refactoring was necessary (prevent copying of code) when the binary
search was implemented since there was no function that only gave back
single values, we only had a function giving back the whole set of
values from the curve.

Added O(n*log n) search for ML value of X. Need to refactor some functions
still.

Added support for three different coverage distributions
when estimating average fragment length; Poisson, NegBin and Uniform
(uniform corresponds to old GapEst)

added coverage to the normal model.
updated plotting script to see likelihood when using coverage.
Added plot for Ml function curves for varying reference sequence lengths.

Added plotting function for ML-curves.
Added high precicion library mpmaths for high precicion calc of ML functions.
Started coding on getDistr.py script.

Updated bwa experiment pipeline. We can now handle bwa process errors.
Added a parameter for number of experiments for each parameter setting
we want to run.
ctnd. implementation of bwa analysis pipeline.

(insert size distribution on contigs and over SVs).

small 'bug' fix in model.py - We now sample points over the
normal pdf in a better way for more accurate estimation,

adding plot.py for plotting expected fragment size. Small fixes in

position is implemented.
